07:26.696 --> 07:30.533
- Hey.
- Hey.

07:30.951 --> 07:34.370
- Saw you at the mall yesterday.
- Yeah, I saw you too.

07:35.247 --> 07:37.665
So you gonna watch
the concert on MTV tonight?

07:37.833 --> 07:39.750
Yeah. You?

07:40.877 --> 07:42.211
Yeah.

07:45.132 --> 07:46.841
My mom's gonna be out of town.

07:49.678 --> 07:51.762
- Cool.
- Cool.

07:52.055 --> 07:53.556
It was so amazing, Daph.

07:53.723 --> 07:56.308
I was like,
"My mom's gonna go out of town."

07:56.518 --> 07:58.727
And he was like,
"Well, maybe we could..."

07:58.895 --> 08:01.730
And I was like, "Yeah, sure."
And he was like, "Cool."

08:01.898 --> 08:04.483
I know. He's so smart.

08:04.651 --> 08:08.654
I don't know. I'm thinking about
that red thing I got at the mall.

08:08.822 --> 08:10.072
It's not slutty.

08:12.325 --> 08:14.201
It's fun.

08:14.411 --> 08:16.829
Well, hello,
he's not coming over to study.

08:17.581 --> 08:19.081
Yeah, I know.

08:19.249 --> 08:22.293
Well, sometimes I'm jealous of you too.

08:22.502 --> 08:26.005
He's not homeless, Howard.
They just don't say where he lives.

08:27.674 --> 08:29.758
Well, it's a silly question.

08:31.052 --> 08:33.971
Because nobody's homeless
in Pleasantville.

08:35.807 --> 08:37.640
Because that's just not what it's like.

08:41.770 --> 08:45.274
Look, Howard, it's almost 6:30.
I gotta go.

09:13.803 --> 09:15.721
- What are you doing?
- What are you doing?

09:15.889 --> 09:18.724
Cut it out, David.
Mark Davis is gonna be here in minutes.

09:18.892 --> 09:21.727
Great. The Pleasantville
marathon starts at 6:30.

09:21.895 --> 09:24.688
I don't believe this. He's gonna be here.

09:24.856 --> 09:26.565
Great. You can watch it upstairs.

09:26.733 --> 09:28.817
Upstairs? Upstairs?

09:28.985 --> 09:30.945
It doesn't have any stereo.

09:35.825 --> 09:37.201
Oh, my God.

09:37.410 --> 09:38.994
Oh, my God.

09:39.162 --> 09:42.790
David, stop stressing.
You can just, like, turn it on normally.

09:42.958 --> 09:45.417
No, I can't. It's a new TV, Jen.

09:45.585 --> 09:47.294
It doesn't work without a remote.

09:48.630 --> 09:50.673
Oh, my God, he's here.

09:58.181 --> 09:59.765
TV repair.

09:59.933 --> 10:01.141
TV repair?

10:01.309 --> 10:04.061
- Yeah. TV busted?
- Yeah.

10:04.646 --> 10:06.355
Well, here I am.

10:12.195 --> 10:15.614
Holy cow, look at that.

10:15.824 --> 10:17.700
Had a little disaster, didn't you, fella?

10:17.867 --> 10:19.159
Well, yeah, sort of.

10:19.327 --> 10:22.663
Well, we'll get you fixed up
in no time.

10:23.873 --> 10:25.624
I know how I'd feel if mine went out.

10:27.210 --> 10:29.378
Almost like losing a friend.

10:30.588 --> 10:32.965
You know, we didn't call any TV repair.

10:33.133 --> 10:36.093
That makes it a lucky day
for both of us, doesn't it?

10:36.845 --> 10:38.554
Do you think you could do this soon?

10:38.722 --> 10:40.431
- It's almost 6:30.
- What's the hurry?

10:40.598 --> 10:42.975
Pleasantville marathon starts at 6:30.

10:46.104 --> 10:50.649
Pleasantville? Gosh, I love that show.
Watched it for years.

10:50.817 --> 10:52.985
That's not the reason.
I've got a date at 6:30.

10:53.153 --> 10:55.279
Who did Muffin take
to the masquerade ball...

10:55.447 --> 10:57.990
when her date came down
with the measles?

10:58.158 --> 11:00.451
- Her father.
- That's right.

11:00.660 --> 11:03.704
- And how'd she dress him?
- As Prince Charming.

11:04.205 --> 11:06.582
Nice. Remember the one...

11:06.750 --> 11:09.918
where Bud lost his cousin when he was
supposed to be watching him?

11:10.086 --> 11:12.296
- Yeah.
- What department store did they go to?

11:12.464 --> 11:14.798
- Mclntyre's.
- McGinty's.

11:14.966 --> 11:17.676
No. Mclntyre's. Remember?

11:17.844 --> 11:20.387
For the very best in men's attire

11:20.555 --> 11:23.474
Head right down to Mclntyre's

11:26.436 --> 11:28.103
That's right.

11:31.149 --> 11:32.566
Listen...

11:35.195 --> 11:38.113
why don't you take
this remote instead?

11:38.281 --> 11:39.948
It's got a little more oomph in it.

11:40.492 --> 11:44.536
- Oomph?
- Sure. Big beautiful set like that?

11:44.704 --> 11:47.539
You want something that'll
put you right in the show.

11:53.296 --> 11:55.631
It's great. We'll take it.

11:57.592 --> 11:59.134
Thank you.

11:59.928 --> 12:01.970
Well, I better get going.

12:02.180 --> 12:03.639
Your show's almost on...

12:04.432 --> 12:06.308
and it's almost time for your date.

12:12.524 --> 12:14.191
Take care, now.

12:38.800 --> 12:40.384
Whether it's on the track...

12:40.718 --> 12:43.804
or just driving around the block,
only new Pennzoil with...

12:43.972 --> 12:45.764
For program information, just...

12:48.852 --> 12:52.271
- Honey, I'm home.
- Great.

12:52.730 --> 12:54.773
- Let me see that.
- No way.

13:06.703 --> 13:09.830
Gee whiz, Mary Sue,
why can't I borrow your radio?

13:09.998 --> 13:11.874
I promised Betty Jean she could use it.

13:12.041 --> 13:15.210
Do you mind? This is only
the most important moment of my life.

13:15.378 --> 13:18.046
Forget it, Jen. I've
waited a year for this.

13:18.214 --> 13:20.048
Come on, David, just give it to me.

13:20.216 --> 13:23.635
- Forget it!
- No way, Bud.

13:24.387 --> 13:25.721
Forget it, Mary Sue.

13:25.889 --> 13:28.515
Come on, Bud. It's mine. Give it back.

13:38.568 --> 13:40.068
Oh, my God.

13:40.236 --> 13:42.362
- What happened?
- I'm not sure.

13:45.325 --> 13:46.700
Hi, sport. Hi, Muffin.

13:46.868 --> 13:50.078
Better get a move on.
You'll be late for school.

13:51.331 --> 13:53.916
- What did you do?
- I don't know.

13:55.502 --> 13:57.920
Look at me. I'm pasty.

13:58.087 --> 14:00.422
Psst. Over here.

14:01.382 --> 14:02.966
Told you it was your lucky day.

14:03.134 --> 14:05.344
I bet you thought
I was just a fan or something.

14:05.512 --> 14:07.179
- What happened?
- A miracle.

14:07.347 --> 14:09.431
Every time I thought
I'd found someone...

14:09.599 --> 14:13.352
they'd turn out to disappoint me.
They'd know all the early episodes...

14:13.520 --> 14:16.400
but they wouldn't know the later ones.
They'd know all about Muffin...

14:16.564 --> 14:18.273
but they wouldn't know about Bud.

14:18.441 --> 14:19.650
What the hell is going on?

14:20.068 --> 14:21.985
Shh. Can't talk like that here.

14:22.153 --> 14:25.280
You're in... Well, you know.

14:25.448 --> 14:28.450
Bud, Mary Sue, breakfast is on the table.

14:28.618 --> 14:30.577
We're in Pleasantville?

14:31.037 --> 14:32.704
A dream come true, huh?

14:32.872 --> 14:34.414
Listen, this really isn't funny.

14:34.582 --> 14:37.000
I have a very important date
in five minutes.

14:37.168 --> 14:39.169
You don't have to worry
about that anymore.

14:43.383 --> 14:45.384
- Bitch.
- No!

14:45.552 --> 14:47.344
You have got to get us out of here.

14:47.512 --> 14:49.638
- Why would I do that?
- Because we don't belong.

14:49.806 --> 14:53.058
Oh, sure, you do.
Mclntyre's department store.

14:53.226 --> 14:57.104
Their father dressed as Prince Charming.
That was gorgeous, Bud.

14:57.272 --> 15:00.023
- My name is David.
- Oh, God.

15:00.191 --> 15:02.859
This is a strange way
of showing your appreciation.

15:03.027 --> 15:05.404
Hey, we appreciate it. We really do.

15:05.572 --> 15:06.822
We just wanna go home now.

15:06.990 --> 15:10.242
But you don't know how long
I've been looking for someone like you.

15:11.202 --> 15:13.495
I'm very disappointed.

15:13.663 --> 15:16.081
In fact, I'm starting
to get a little upset.

15:16.249 --> 15:17.708
No, don't get upset.

15:17.875 --> 15:20.544
Well, wouldn't you?
You look for someone for years.

15:20.712 --> 15:23.046
You pour your heart into it.

15:23.214 --> 15:25.549
This is a privilege, you know.

15:25.717 --> 15:28.260
I don't think I better
talk about this now.

15:28.428 --> 15:29.595
Where are you going?

15:29.804 --> 15:33.181
I don't think we should discuss this
until I'm more composed.

15:33.349 --> 15:34.433
Wait a minute.

15:34.601 --> 15:37.144
Maybe in a while
when I'm not so emotional.

15:37.353 --> 15:40.856
Give you a week or two
to change your attitude.

15:41.024 --> 15:42.024
Come back!

15:43.443 --> 15:45.027
Come back!

15:50.199 --> 15:51.283
A week or two?

15:51.451 --> 15:52.993
Think Mom and Da?

15:53.161 --> 15:54.202
Being silly.

15:54.370 --> 15:56.038
From day to day.

15:57.498 --> 16:01.126
- Oh, God.
- What's gonna happen?

16:01.336 --> 16:04.004
I don't know. It's not possible.
Is it possible?

16:04.172 --> 16:07.424
Bud, Mary Sue,
your breakfast is getting cold.

16:08.551 --> 16:10.552
It can't be possible.

16:21.397 --> 16:23.482
Well, come on, kids.

16:23.650 --> 16:27.569
You're not going off to school
without a hot breakfast inside you.

16:29.197 --> 16:30.572
Forward march.

16:50.093 --> 16:52.719
I just love you in that sweater, Mary Sue.

16:52.887 --> 16:55.138
It's so flattering.

16:55.306 --> 16:57.057
Thanks.

17:00.269 --> 17:04.481
Morning, kids. Better get a move on,
or you'll be late for school.

17:04.648 --> 17:07.651
- I don't believe this.
- Neither do I.

17:07.819 --> 17:09.903
Well, come on, dig in.

17:10.070 --> 17:13.448
I put blueberries in them
just the way you like.

17:15.201 --> 17:17.368
Well, come on, sweetie.
It's getting late.

17:18.746 --> 17:22.165
Actually, I'm not hungry.

17:24.292 --> 17:26.294
Nonsense, young lady.

17:26.462 --> 17:30.716
You're gonna start your day off with
a nice big breakfast. Here we go. Sit down.

17:32.635 --> 17:35.804
Here's some pancakes and eggs.

17:37.140 --> 17:41.977
Sausage and some good crisp bacon.

17:44.397 --> 17:46.940
And, of course, a ham steak.

17:50.486 --> 17:53.613
You eat on up,
then it's right off to school.

18:01.706 --> 18:03.540
Hurry, hurry.

18:13.301 --> 18:15.218
I'm gonna hurl, David, I swear to God.

18:15.386 --> 18:16.887
Just take deep breaths.

18:17.054 --> 18:20.640
It's all that animal fat.
I can feel it in my pores.

18:20.808 --> 18:22.684
I still don't see why
we're doing this.

18:22.852 --> 18:24.436
We're supposed to be in school.

18:24.604 --> 18:26.354
We're supposed to be at home, David.

18:26.522 --> 18:28.899
- We're supposed to be in color.
- Okay, okay, okay.

18:29.066 --> 18:31.276
- God.
- Hello, Bud.

18:32.612 --> 18:34.321
Hello, Mr. Simpson.

18:34.489 --> 18:36.156
Hear your dad got a new car.

18:37.700 --> 18:40.660
Oh, yeah. A Buick. It's swell.

18:41.204 --> 18:42.621
Great.

18:44.415 --> 18:46.249
Do you know that guy?

18:46.417 --> 18:49.336
Yeah. He owns the hardware store.

18:49.587 --> 18:51.338
You listen to me for just a minute.

18:51.506 --> 18:53.586
I don't know what you've done,
but you better fix it.

18:53.716 --> 18:54.716
- Shh! Shh!
- Fast.

18:54.884 --> 18:57.135
I had a date with Mark,
and I bought new underwear.

18:57.303 --> 19:00.806
We have to just play along for a little
while until that guy shows up again.

19:00.973 --> 19:02.432
- Play along?
- Yes.

19:02.600 --> 19:06.061
I am Bud Parker,
and you are Mary Sue.

19:06.229 --> 19:10.398
No. No. I'm not gonna do it.
If I don't dress like this for Mom...

19:10.566 --> 19:12.984
l'm not gonna do it for you.
- We have no choice.

19:13.152 --> 19:15.654
We are stuck here
until that guy shows up again.

19:15.822 --> 19:17.697
Why can't we just explain it
to somebody?

19:18.407 --> 19:19.741
To who?

19:32.338 --> 19:34.005
Go. Go. Go.

19:42.306 --> 19:43.765
Here, kitty.

19:44.267 --> 19:46.059
Here, kitty, kitty, kitty.

19:46.435 --> 19:48.395
Here, kitty.

19:49.647 --> 19:51.231
Oh, God.

19:52.149 --> 19:53.483
We are.

19:54.735 --> 19:57.404
We're, like, stuck in Nerdville.

20:03.119 --> 20:07.873
I knew you'd pay a price for this. I knew you
couldn't be so hopelessly geek-ridden...

20:08.040 --> 20:12.335
for so long without suffering
some really tragic consequences.

20:13.671 --> 20:15.755
But it's just not fair.

20:16.799 --> 20:18.800
I was getting really popular.

20:19.010 --> 20:22.929
And Debbie Russell had transferred
to another school.

20:23.097 --> 20:25.557
And my skin was really great
since March.

20:25.725 --> 20:28.018
Mark Davis was finally starting
to come around.

20:28.185 --> 20:29.978
Hello, Mary Sue.

20:34.901 --> 20:37.485
What's all the commotion?
Where's the cat?

20:38.821 --> 20:40.322
Um...

20:41.365 --> 20:42.407
It's...

20:48.039 --> 20:50.665
Oh. Right.

20:53.336 --> 20:55.545
I'll see you at school, Mary Sue.

21:05.097 --> 21:06.348
Who's that?

21:07.433 --> 21:10.727
Skip Martin, captain of
the basketball team.

21:11.646 --> 21:13.396
Does he like me?

21:14.190 --> 21:16.524
As a matter of fact, he does.

21:32.458 --> 21:33.917
Those are my friends?

21:34.085 --> 21:37.879
Peggy Jane, Lisa Anne, Betty Jean.

21:38.255 --> 21:40.382
Can we do any better?

21:40.549 --> 21:42.884
I don't think so.

21:44.220 --> 21:45.720
Okay.

21:49.517 --> 21:52.310
- Mary Sue.
- Hi.

21:53.771 --> 21:57.565
Last week, class, we discussed
the geography of Main Street.

21:58.150 --> 22:01.736
This week we're going to be
talking about Elm Street.

22:01.904 --> 22:04.823
Now, can anyone tell me
the difference...

22:04.991 --> 22:07.575
between Elm Street
and Main Street?

22:07.785 --> 22:08.868
Tommy.

22:09.412 --> 22:10.954
It's not as long?

22:11.122 --> 22:13.498
That's right, Tommy. It's not as long.

22:13.708 --> 22:16.292
Also, it only has houses.

22:16.544 --> 22:20.547
So the geography of Main Street
is different...

22:20.715 --> 22:23.049
than the geography of Elm Street.

22:24.385 --> 22:25.802
Mary Sue.

22:25.970 --> 22:28.346
Yeah. What's outside of Pleasantville?

22:36.355 --> 22:37.939
I don't understand.

22:38.816 --> 22:41.192
Outside of Pleasantville.

22:41.360 --> 22:43.194
Like, what's at the end of Main Street?

22:44.905 --> 22:48.491
Mary Sue, you should know
the answer to that.

22:48.701 --> 22:53.121
The end of Main Street
is just the beginning again.

23:58.020 --> 23:59.854
Come on, men, let's go.

24:03.317 --> 24:06.653
That's it, men, keep it up.
Big game tomorrow.

24:16.997 --> 24:18.414
Bud.

24:18.833 --> 24:19.874
Hi, Bud.

24:20.084 --> 24:21.167
Hi, Skip.

24:21.335 --> 24:22.752
Hi, Bud.

24:23.712 --> 24:24.754
Hi, Skip.

24:25.047 --> 24:28.341
- Bud, can I ask you a question?
- Sure.

24:29.510 --> 24:31.219
Well...

24:31.387 --> 24:33.555
if I was to go up to your sister...

24:33.722 --> 24:35.890
What I mean is,
if I was to go up to Mary Sue...

24:36.058 --> 24:38.685
Oh, my God. Are we in that episode?

24:38.853 --> 24:41.437
- What?
- Oh, I don't believe this.

24:41.605 --> 24:42.647
What's the matter?

24:42.815 --> 24:46.317
You wanna ask her out tonight, and then
you wanna give her your school pin.

24:46.485 --> 24:48.736
Yeah. How'd you know?

24:50.072 --> 24:54.576
Look, Skip, I don't think
it's a real good time for that right now.

24:55.786 --> 24:56.911
What do you mean?

24:57.079 --> 25:00.165
Well, what I mean is...

25:00.332 --> 25:03.293
Mary Sue's a little different lately.

25:03.919 --> 25:05.962
She won't go out with me?

25:06.130 --> 25:08.673
No, no. Hey. I didn't say that.
It's just that she's...

25:08.841 --> 25:12.135
I don't know what I'd do
if she wouldn't go out with me.

25:30.321 --> 25:32.906
Come here, guys.
Don't touch it. Stay back.

25:33.699 --> 25:35.408
I'm sure we'll work something out.

25:36.744 --> 25:38.953
- I thought you liked him.
- Yeah, but I don't know.

25:39.121 --> 25:41.748
One date, Jen. Please.
That's all I'm asking.

25:41.957 --> 25:45.543
If you don't go out with this guy,
we could throw their universe out of whack.

25:45.711 --> 25:48.087
It's too weird.
This place gives me the creeps.

25:48.255 --> 25:50.131
- Did you know the books are blank?
- What?

25:50.299 --> 25:53.176
I was in the library.
They have covers and nothing inside.

25:53.344 --> 25:55.053
What were you doing in a library?

25:55.221 --> 25:58.056
I got lost. Oh, wait. Look at this.

25:58.224 --> 26:01.100
Know why the firemen
only rescue cats out of trees?

26:01.268 --> 26:03.019
- Nothing burns around here.
- Jen, stop.

26:03.187 --> 26:06.648
They don't even need firemen.
I could really use a cigarette too.

26:06.857 --> 26:10.276
Jen, listen. I will get us out of here.

26:10.486 --> 26:12.737
I really will.
But if we don't play along...

26:12.905 --> 26:17.116
we can alter their whole existence,
and then we may never get home.

26:18.494 --> 26:21.955
You really think anybody's gonna notice if I
don't have a chocolate malt with this guy?

26:25.292 --> 26:27.001
You won't believe what we heard.

26:27.169 --> 26:28.503
Skip Martin is gonna ask you out.

26:28.671 --> 26:30.797
- And that's not all.
- No, that's not all.

26:30.965 --> 26:33.591
He's gonna give you his pin.

26:37.554 --> 26:39.681
Are you sure I'm supposed to wear this?

26:40.349 --> 26:42.350
I could kill a guy with these things.

26:42.518 --> 26:44.352
It's in your closet.

26:44.520 --> 26:46.062
I've worn kinky stuff before...

26:46.230 --> 26:49.023
- He won't notice anyway.
- Why not?

26:49.191 --> 26:52.235
They just don't notice
that kind of thing around here.

26:53.737 --> 26:56.364
- So, what's the point?
- Jen, please.

26:56.532 --> 26:58.866
Hello. I've got 3 pounds
of underwire on here.

26:59.034 --> 27:01.953
Just go with the program, huh?
I'm late for work.

27:02.329 --> 27:03.371
Work?

27:14.008 --> 27:15.049
Bud.

27:15.217 --> 27:18.678
Yeah. Yeah. Sorry.
I just had to help my folks...

27:18.887 --> 27:21.055
and then I couldn't find my hat.

27:21.223 --> 27:24.392
Oh. I didn't know what to do.

27:25.311 --> 27:26.352
What's wrong?

27:27.021 --> 27:29.397
Well, I always
wipe down the counter...

27:29.565 --> 27:31.941
and then you set out
the napkins and glasses...

27:32.109 --> 27:34.777
and then I make the French fries, and...
- Yeah.

27:35.237 --> 27:39.032
But you didn't come,
so I just kept on wiping.

27:44.747 --> 27:46.331
I'm sorry.

27:47.166 --> 27:49.042
Yeah, well... Ha, ha.

27:50.753 --> 27:51.753
Um...

27:52.129 --> 27:55.340
You know, if this ever happens again...

27:58.135 --> 27:59.927
you can make the fries...

28:00.095 --> 28:02.180
even if I haven't put out
the napkins yet.

28:02.765 --> 28:04.098
Oh.

28:05.517 --> 28:07.101
Thank you.

28:33.295 --> 28:36.923
- There aren't any cheeseburgers.
- What?

28:37.091 --> 28:40.093
Usually, I put out the burger,
and you finish with the lettuce.

28:40.302 --> 28:44.389
- Okay, listen. Do you have the lettuce?
- Yeah.

28:44.598 --> 28:47.600
- Have you cooked the burgers?
- Yeah.

28:47.768 --> 28:49.685
Put on the lettuce,
finish the burger...

28:49.853 --> 28:52.647
and pretend it was me doing it
the whole time.

28:53.607 --> 28:55.817
Yeah. You can do it, really.

28:56.402 --> 28:57.860
Okay.

29:13.085 --> 29:15.837
I sure am glad you said
you'd come out with me tonight.

29:16.004 --> 29:18.965
Oh, well, gee whiz, Skip.
I sure am glad you asked me.

29:19.508 --> 29:24.762
I don't know if I ever said this
to you before, but, well...

29:24.930 --> 29:28.015
I think you're just about
the keenest girl in the whole school.

29:28.183 --> 29:30.101
Really, Skip? The keenest?

29:30.853 --> 29:32.311
Oh, yeah.

29:33.397 --> 29:35.648
What can I get you two?

29:36.150 --> 29:37.817
I don't know, Bud.

29:37.985 --> 29:40.778
I guess I'll have my usual:
Cheeseburger and a cherry Coke.

29:41.530 --> 29:45.741
Oh, I don't know, Bud. I guess I'll
have a salad and an Evian water.

29:48.579 --> 29:50.455
Cheeseburger it is.

29:52.749 --> 29:56.002
You see, the whole time
we were in Civics together...

29:56.170 --> 29:58.713
I really wanted to come over
and sit next to you...

29:58.881 --> 30:02.383
but you were always sitting between
Lisa Anne and Peggy Jane.

30:02.885 --> 30:05.887
And you always seemed
so smart and everything.

30:06.096 --> 30:09.140
Like that report you did
on our town hall.

30:09.308 --> 30:12.393
Gosh. I didn't know
what I'd talk to you about.

30:12.811 --> 30:17.523
Yeah. Well, sometimes
talking's overrated.

30:17.691 --> 30:19.609
Don't you think?

30:19.943 --> 30:20.985
Huh?

30:22.321 --> 30:23.571
Oh, right.

30:25.157 --> 30:27.992
So I know I haven't been steady
with anybody or anything...

30:28.160 --> 30:29.952
but I just don't wanna rush it.

30:30.120 --> 30:32.705
I mean, there's kids
that are holding hands already...

30:32.873 --> 30:37.043
but I figure there's plenty of time
for that kind of thing later on, don't you?

30:38.003 --> 30:42.131
Yeah. Can you excuse me
for just a second?

30:54.686 --> 30:56.145
God.

30:56.563 --> 30:58.523
Oh, God.

31:00.025 --> 31:02.025
- Did he give it to you?
- I bet he gave it to you.

31:02.110 --> 31:03.569
I don't think he knows how.

31:04.238 --> 31:06.447
I bet he's gonna take her
to Lovers' Lane.

31:06.615 --> 31:08.366
I bet he is. I bet he is.

31:08.575 --> 31:10.535
I bet he's even gonna hold her hand.

31:10.702 --> 31:12.119
Ohh!

31:20.671 --> 31:24.173
So, anyhow, I really wanted
to sit next to you in Civics, but...

31:24.341 --> 31:26.592
- You wanna get out of here?
- What?

31:26.760 --> 31:29.303
Do you wanna leave?
Do you wanna go somewhere?

31:29.471 --> 31:30.846
But where could we go?

31:31.515 --> 31:36.018
Lovers' Lane?

31:36.186 --> 31:40.106
Yeah, Lovers' Lane. You up for it?

31:41.233 --> 31:44.360
Come on.

31:52.286 --> 31:53.578
Oh, shit.

31:54.121 --> 31:55.538
Jennifer!

31:56.832 --> 32:00.084
Jennifer, stop! Stop!

32:00.252 --> 32:02.795
You can't do this, Jennifer!
He doesn't exist!

32:02.963 --> 32:06.424
You can't do this to someone
who doesn't exist!

32:12.764 --> 32:14.307
It sure is pretty.

32:14.725 --> 32:18.019
Oh, yeah. Gorgeous.

32:19.730 --> 32:22.106
To be honest, Mary Sue...

32:22.274 --> 32:25.776
I didn't think you'd wanna come here
until we'd been pinned for a while.

32:25.944 --> 32:29.614
Oh, Skip, you can pin me
anytime you want to.

32:33.535 --> 32:35.494
Or maybe I should just pin you.

32:37.164 --> 32:40.541
That's silly, Mary Sue.
How could you possibly pin me?

33:02.022 --> 33:04.398
Bud? Son, what's wrong?

33:04.733 --> 33:06.150
Have you seen Mary Sue?

33:06.318 --> 33:09.612
Why, no. She's still on her date with Skip.
Is something the matter?

33:09.780 --> 33:11.989
No. No. I was just worried about her.

33:19.498 --> 33:22.249
Bud, your sister's getting older now...

33:22.417 --> 33:24.669
and she'll naturally
be going out with boys.

33:26.046 --> 33:27.755
But she's a fine young woman.

33:27.923 --> 33:30.883
She would never do anything
for us to be concerned about.

33:32.844 --> 33:34.303
Honest.

33:51.655 --> 33:54.115
I think I better go home now, Mary Sue.

33:54.282 --> 33:55.366
Why?

33:55.617 --> 33:58.786
I think I might be ill.

34:00.247 --> 34:01.622
Something's happening to me.

34:02.833 --> 34:04.542
That's supposed to happen.

34:06.128 --> 34:07.670
It is?

34:08.797 --> 34:10.630
Yeah. Trust me.

34:13.051 --> 34:14.552
Do you want some more cookies?

34:16.221 --> 34:17.679
No, thanks. I'm fine.

34:20.183 --> 34:23.101
How about
some marshmallow rice squares?

34:23.311 --> 34:24.520
Those are swell.

34:24.688 --> 34:26.772
No, I'm fine, thank you.

34:28.275 --> 34:30.484
- Now, who could that be?
- I've got it.

34:34.697 --> 34:36.031
- Oh, hi.
- Hi there.

34:36.199 --> 34:38.534
You took off so quick,
I wasn't sure you were okay.

34:38.702 --> 34:41.829
Oh, yeah. No, I'm fine.
I just... I had to get home early.

34:41.996 --> 34:45.750
Bud, you know how when we close up...

34:45.917 --> 34:48.627
I close the register,
then you lower the blinds...

34:48.795 --> 34:51.034
and I turn out the lights,
and we both lock the doors?

34:51.172 --> 34:55.551
- Yeah.
- Well, you weren't around this time...

34:55.761 --> 35:00.890
so I did the whole thing by myself.

35:02.517 --> 35:04.018
Wow.

35:04.436 --> 35:08.522
And not only that,
I didn't even do it in the same order.

35:08.732 --> 35:13.402
First I lowered the blinds,
then I closed the register. And...

35:16.031 --> 35:17.573
Oh, hello, Betty.

35:18.283 --> 35:19.658
Hello, Bill.

35:25.165 --> 35:27.833
Okay, well, that's great.
Thank you for stopping by.

35:28.001 --> 35:30.044
I... You know, I appreciate it.

35:34.341 --> 35:36.050
I'll see you tomorrow.

35:37.594 --> 35:41.055
Well, gee, thanks, Skip.
I sure had a wonderful time.

35:44.559 --> 35:45.851
Me too.

35:46.937 --> 35:48.270
Night.

36:04.329 --> 36:06.247
Hello, Mr. Johnson.

36:06.414 --> 36:08.123
Oh, hello, Mary Sue.

36:09.376 --> 36:12.127
- What did you do to him?
- Nothing.

36:12.295 --> 36:15.339
What do you mean, "nothing"?
That's not nothing.

36:15.549 --> 36:18.843
Why don't you relax, Bud?
We had a nice time.

36:20.178 --> 36:23.681
I am really sleepy, and I have to wake up
early in the morning to go to school.

36:23.849 --> 36:25.975
So night.

37:05.265 --> 37:06.932
Pleasure.

37:08.894 --> 37:11.562
Hi. Looks like it's gonna be
another beautiful sunny day.

37:11.730 --> 37:14.315
High 72, low 72,
not a cloud in the sky.

37:14.482 --> 37:15.608
Bud?

37:17.027 --> 37:19.987
It's 8:00 in the morning.
Are you watching television?

37:48.516 --> 37:49.516
Oh, no.

37:50.852 --> 37:52.603
Come on, men. Let's get in positions.

37:52.771 --> 37:55.481
We got a big game next week. Let's go.

37:55.649 --> 37:57.191
Come on.

38:03.406 --> 38:05.032
Oh, my God.

38:06.076 --> 38:09.078
You can't do this, Jennifer. I warned you.

38:09.245 --> 38:10.371
So, what's the big deal?

38:10.538 --> 38:13.332
Oh, okay. They're not good
at basketball anymore.

38:13.500 --> 38:15.834
- My God. What a tragedy.
- You don't understand.

38:16.002 --> 38:18.337
You're messing with
their whole goddamn universe.

38:18.505 --> 38:21.423
Maybe it needs to be messed with.
Did that ever occur to you?

38:21.591 --> 38:25.219
- Hey, M.S. How you doing?
- Cool, P.J. How are you doing?

38:26.012 --> 38:29.390
- Cool. Cool.
- Cool.

38:29.557 --> 38:32.476
"Cool"? What are you doing
to these people? You can't do this.

38:32.644 --> 38:35.104
- If I don't, who will?
- But they're happy like this.

38:35.271 --> 38:38.691
No. David, nobody is happy
in a poodle skirt and a sweater set.

38:40.735 --> 38:42.194
You really like this, don't you?

38:43.238 --> 38:46.198
No, it's not like
you think it's funny or dorky.

38:46.408 --> 38:48.200
You, like, really like it.

38:48.368 --> 38:49.785
No. You have it all wrong.

38:49.953 --> 38:51.537
I am mortified to be your sister.

38:51.705 --> 38:53.580
You have no right to do this to them.

38:53.790 --> 38:55.249
Listen to me for just a minute.

38:55.417 --> 38:58.377
These people don't wanna be geeks.
They wanna be attractive.

38:58.545 --> 39:00.796
They have potential.
They just don't know better.

39:00.964 --> 39:02.464
They don't have that potential.

39:02.632 --> 39:05.217
Oh, yeah? Look at that.

39:08.847 --> 39:11.140
Wow. What happened to your gum?

39:11.433 --> 39:12.474
I gotta go.

39:12.642 --> 39:14.727
I'm gonna meet Skip at the flagpole.

39:53.475 --> 39:54.850
Mm-hm.

39:55.894 --> 39:57.144
Hm.

39:57.687 --> 40:00.314
Well, I don't think
it's anything to worry about.

40:00.482 --> 40:02.691
You cut down on greasy foods
and chocolate.

40:02.859 --> 40:04.777
You know, things like that.

40:04.986 --> 40:07.529
It'll probably just clear up on its own.

40:13.328 --> 40:15.245
Jesus Christ.

40:41.189 --> 40:44.316
Do you think we could have
two cheeseburgers and some cherry Cokes?

40:47.112 --> 40:48.487
I'll be right with you.

40:49.280 --> 40:50.697
Thanks.

40:56.746 --> 40:59.456
Two cheeseburgers,
two cherry Cokes.

41:02.460 --> 41:04.628
There aren't any cheeseburgers.

41:08.925 --> 41:12.302
- I thought we talked about this. I thought...
- What's the point, Bud?

41:14.013 --> 41:16.140
You make hamburgers.
That is the point.

41:16.307 --> 41:21.895
No, I know. I know I do.
But it's always the same, you know?

41:22.814 --> 41:25.607
Grill the bun, flip the meat,
melt the cheese. Never changes.

41:25.775 --> 41:29.027
- It never gets any better or worse.
- Okay, just listen for a sec.

41:29.195 --> 41:31.572
The night when I closed by myself
was different.

41:31.739 --> 41:33.657
Oh, forget about that.

41:34.159 --> 41:35.993
Oh, okay.

41:37.245 --> 41:39.037
I really liked it, though.

41:41.166 --> 41:42.749
Come here.

41:47.088 --> 41:48.088
Look.

41:48.631 --> 41:50.966
You can't always like what you do.

41:51.176 --> 41:54.219
Sometimes you just gotta do it
because it's your job.

41:54.387 --> 41:57.347
And even if you don't like it,
you just gotta do it anyway.

41:57.974 --> 42:01.143
- Why?
- So they can have their hamburgers.

42:01.936 --> 42:04.021
- Oh.
- I'm sorry.

42:04.189 --> 42:05.480
You know what I really like?

42:06.232 --> 42:08.567
- What's that?
- Christmastime.

42:10.069 --> 42:11.695
See, every year, on December 3rd...

42:11.863 --> 42:14.448
I get to paint Christmas decorations
on the window...

42:14.616 --> 42:17.701
and every year I get to paint
a different thing.

42:17.869 --> 42:19.328
Here, I'll show you.

42:25.335 --> 42:26.543
Wow. That's pretty good.

42:26.711 --> 42:28.629
Thanks. But this morning
I was thinking...

42:28.796 --> 42:31.340
and I realized that
I look forward to it all year.

42:31.507 --> 42:33.258
I thought, "That seems awfully silly.

42:33.426 --> 42:36.803
It seems like an awfully long time
to be waiting for just one moment."

42:36.971 --> 42:38.305
Don't you think?

42:39.557 --> 42:41.391
Well, don't you?

42:43.061 --> 42:46.230
I think that you should try not
to think about that anymore.

42:47.482 --> 42:48.941
Okay.

42:49.108 --> 42:50.776
I'll try that, then.

42:53.696 --> 42:55.322
- Morning, Jim.
- How are you?

42:55.490 --> 42:56.823
Awfully nice.

42:56.991 --> 42:58.492
Have they ever lost before?

42:58.660 --> 43:00.827
Basketball? No, they sure haven't.

43:00.995 --> 43:03.330
It just feels wrong, that's all.

43:03.539 --> 43:05.624
Maybe that's where
they get that saying:

43:05.792 --> 43:07.334
"Can't win them all."

43:07.543 --> 43:10.045
That's a good point, Ralph.
They do have that saying.

43:10.213 --> 43:13.632
But they do win them all.
They've always won them all.

43:14.884 --> 43:17.177
Oh, Mr. Mayor. Here. Here. Go ahead.

